==English==

===Etymology===
[[auto-]] Ancient Greek [[αὐτός]], "self" +
[[gloss]] Koine Greek [[γλώσσα]] ([[glossa]]), "tongue" +
[[-onym]] Greek [[όνομα]] ([[onoma]]) "name"

===Noun===
'''autoglossonym'''
# The [[name]] of a [[language]], in its language (as opposed to, say, in English).  Example: [[Nederlands]] (which in English is [[Dutch]]).

